metadata

  block-headings: true
  biblio-style: imsart-number
  colorlinks: true
  urlcolor: blue
  citecolor: blue
  title: A Sample Article Title
  short-title: A Sample Running Head Title
  author:
    - name: Name1 Surname1
      email: first@somewhere.com
      orcid: 0000-0000-0000-0000
      note: Some comment
      affiliations:
        - name: University or Company Name
          department: Department
          city: City
          country: Country
    - name: Name2 Surname2
      email: second@somewhere.com
      affiliations:
        - name: Another University
          department: Department
          city: City
          country: Country
    - name: Name3 Surname3
      email: third@somewhere.com
      affiliations:
        - name: Third University
          department: Department
          city: City
          country: Country
  abstract: |
    The abstract should summarize the contents of the paper. It should be clear, descriptive, self-explanatory and not longer than 200 words. It should also be suitable for publication in abstracting services. Formulas should be used as sparingly as possible within the abstract. The abstract should not make reference to results, bibliography or formulas in the body of the paper---it should be self-contained.
  keywords:
    - first keyword
    - second keyword
  bibliography:
    - references.bib
  ims-journal: sts
  header-includes:
    - |
      \usepackage{longtable}
      \theoremstyle{plain}
      \newtheorem{axiom}{Axiom}
      \newtheorem{claim}[axiom]{Claim}
      \newtheorem{theorem}{Theorem}[section]
      \newtheorem{lemma}[theorem]{Lemma}
      \theoremstyle{definition}
      \newtheorem{definition}[theorem]{Definition}
      \newtheorem*{example}{Example}
      \newtheorem*{fact}{Fact}
  


